    <h1>Linear Regression</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Deisenroth et al., <em>Mathematics for Machine Learning</em> (CC BY 4.0) &middot; <a href="https://mml-book.github.io/">mml-book.github.io</a></p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">Find weights that <strong>minimize squared error</strong>. The <strong>normal equation</strong> gives the closed-form solution: w = (X&#x1D40;X)&#x207B;&#xB9;X&#x1D40;y. <strong>Gradient descent</strong> gives the iterative one: update weights in the direction that reduces error fastest. Both arrive at the same answer for linear models.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- SVG: scatter plot with fitted line and residuals -->
